---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Strategy - FastQC">
  <p class="label">Strategy</p>
  <h1>Keeping pace with upstream</h1>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem">
    <h2>Goal</h2>
    <p style="color: var(--ink-muted)">
      Produce byte-identical <code>fastqc_data.txt</code> and <code>summary.txt</code>
      for the same inputs as
      <a href="https://github.com/s-andrews/FastQC">FastQC</a>,
      so the two can be used interchangeably.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem">
    <h2>Upstream tracking</h2>
    <p style="color: var(--ink-muted); margin-bottom: 0.75rem">
      <code>UPSTREAM.toml</code> pins the tracked Java FastQC version.
      A nightly CI job checks for new releases and opens a GitHub issue when one appears.
    </p>
    <p style="color: var(--ink-muted); margin-bottom: 0.5rem">When a new release is published:</p>
    <ol style="color: var(--ink-muted)">
      <li>Review upstream changes</li>
      <li>Update <code>UPSTREAM.toml</code>, <code>Cargo.toml</code>, and <code>src/lib.rs</code></li>
      <li>Implement any algorithm changes</li>
      <li>Regenerate reference data and patch files</li>
      <li>Run equivalence tests</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem">
    <h2>Equivalence testing</h2>
    <p style="color: var(--ink-muted); margin-bottom: 0.75rem">
      Every commit is tested against stored reference output across 18 test cases:
    </p>
    <ul style="color: var(--ink-muted)">
      <li>Text files must be byte-identical after applying known-difference patches</li>
      <li>HTML report must match structurally after normalizing embedded images</li>
      <li>SVG charts must match after normalizing font and rendering attributes</li>
      <li>PNG charts are compared pixel-by-pixel with a tolerance threshold</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="color: var(--ink-muted); margin-top: 0.75rem">
      See the <a href="equivalence/">equivalence page</a> for details.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem">
    <h2>Known differences</h2>
    <ul style="color: var(--ink-muted)">
      <li>Rust bundles Liberation Sans; Java uses system Arial. Character widths differ slightly, shifting text positions in charts.</li>
      <li>PNG rendering uses resvg + tiny-skia instead of Java2D. Antialiasing differs.</li>
      <li>SVG output includes bold titles and <code>stroke-width="2"</code> on data lines to match the Java PNG appearance.</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="color: var(--ink-muted); margin-top: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.9rem">
      <a href="https://github.com/s-andrews/FastQC/pull/185">s-andrews/FastQC#185</a> bundles Liberation Sans
      in Java FastQC. Once a release includes this change, most font-metric differences will shrink or disappear.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
